						<div class="postbody">Oh, I get it now. Since you're not using $2006, the coarse scroll doesn't change when you finish the writes, but when the PPU does v:0000010000011111=t:0000010000011111, so you have to do the $2005 write before that, but since the fine X scroll changes immediately, you can't update that part at the same time. Got it.<br /><br />Anyway, landing a couple of PPU writes on hblank shouldn't be so hard, there's quite a bit of tolerance there.</div>

